48:29.840 --> 48:31.642
Let's say we take insulin.

48:31.676 --> 48:35.313
For ease of calculation, I'll
say it's 100 dollars a vial.

48:35.346 --> 48:38.583
The pharmaceutical company may
sell it to the wholesaler for

48:38.616 --> 48:41.319
110 dollars.

48:41.352 --> 48:46.457
The wholesaler then sells it to
the pharmacy for 120 dollars.

48:46.491 --> 48:48.793
Now, they kept 10
dollars of the hundred.

48:48.826 --> 48:52.797
The pharmacy now sells to people
who don't have insurance for 130

48:52.830 --> 48:56.467
dollars, so now they
get to keep 10 dollars.

48:56.501 --> 49:00.505
So that's what faces people
who don't have insurance.

49:01.372 --> 49:04.009
On the other hand...

49:04.509 --> 49:09.014
insurance companies work through
pharmacy benefit managers.

49:09.347 --> 49:11.983
Now, pharmacy benefit
managers negotiate with the

49:12.017 --> 49:16.454
pharmaceutical company that "I
will pay you only 60 dollars for

49:16.487 --> 49:18.023
your insulin."

49:18.056 --> 49:21.826
And so, together, the patient
and the pharmacy benefit manager

49:21.859 --> 49:24.996
will pay pharmacies 130...

49:25.030 --> 49:28.799
but PBMs get 50 dollars back
from the pharmaceutical company

49:28.833 --> 49:30.901
as a rebate.

49:31.369 --> 49:36.407
Over time, PBMs have realized
that the higher the price of the

49:36.441 --> 49:40.545
drug, they can profit more,
because pharmaceutical companies

49:40.578 --> 49:45.383
are willing to give rebates
on higher-priced medications.

49:45.416 --> 49:48.019
And now that the
price of insulin goes up,

49:48.053 --> 49:51.556
everyone in the supply chain is
benefiting from a high price,

49:51.589 --> 49:55.693
and the only person who's not
benefitting is the patient.

49:55.726 --> 49:58.863
Pharmacy benefit managers have
all kinds of deals that--

49:58.896 --> 50:02.567
you know, to increase revenue
with the drug companies.

50:02.600 --> 50:04.169
And of course, no one really
knows what these deals are

50:04.202 --> 50:06.871
because they're
not transparent.

50:07.705 --> 50:11.042
You know, these middlepeople,
they're not really doing any

50:11.076 --> 50:13.411
healthcare for the patient,
they're just sort of--

50:13.444 --> 50:17.048
it's just another layer
of-- of bureaucracy,

50:17.082 --> 50:21.052
from which, you know, a
lot of money changes hands.

50:21.086 --> 50:24.189
Diabetes is growing, and so the
market is ever bigger and bigger

50:24.222 --> 50:25.156
and bigger.

50:25.190 --> 50:27.725
There's a huge
amount of money at stake.

