01:04:53.590 --> 01:04:57.928
***

01:04:57.962 --> 01:05:00.630
My mom does not
get paid enough

01:05:00.664 --> 01:05:03.900
to pay for everything.

01:05:05.802 --> 01:05:09.606
When I turn 26 and I have
to pay for my own stuff,

01:05:09.639 --> 01:05:12.776
I'm a little scared.

01:05:14.644 --> 01:05:17.747
Like, I have nightmares
about being homeless again.

01:05:17.781 --> 01:05:21.618
***

01:05:21.651 --> 01:05:25.622
I never thought
that my child...

01:05:25.655 --> 01:05:28.325
[voice wavering]
would really...

01:05:28.358 --> 01:05:31.795
hold onto that...

01:05:31.828 --> 01:05:34.931
necessity of
getting a job so young.

01:05:34.965 --> 01:05:36.666
[Sandra] Good luck!
Love you!

01:05:36.700 --> 01:05:39.003
[Emma] Love you too!

01:05:39.336 --> 01:05:40.604
[girl] See, you gotta get
used to the pressure because

01:05:40.637 --> 01:05:42.472
it flies.

01:05:42.506 --> 01:05:45.109
[Sandra VO] I'm so proud of her,

01:05:45.142 --> 01:05:46.810
but at 14,

01:05:46.843 --> 01:05:50.480
you shouldn't get a job to have
to pay for medical supplies.

01:05:50.814 --> 01:05:54.518
Just...shake it out.

01:05:54.551 --> 01:05:58.355
14-year-olds should be working
for their fun things, not...

01:05:58.388 --> 01:06:00.657
to stay alive.

01:06:00.690 --> 01:06:04.661
***

01:06:04.694 --> 01:06:07.364
After a two-year battle, the
Minnesota House and Senate today

01:06:07.397 --> 01:06:09.966
both passed the Alec
Smith Emergency Insulin Bill.

01:06:10.000 --> 01:06:11.735
[gavel bangs]

01:06:11.768 --> 01:06:13.837
[woman VO] Amidst the pandemic
precautions of masks and social

01:06:13.870 --> 01:06:16.806
distancing, the legislature
moved forward with an emergency

01:06:16.840 --> 01:06:17.841
insulin bill.

01:06:17.874 --> 01:06:20.010
This is a good
day in Minnesota.

01:06:20.044 --> 01:06:22.646
[woman VO] Nicole Smith-Holt
sat in the House gallery as the

01:06:22.679 --> 01:06:24.381
vote was announced.

01:06:24.414 --> 01:06:28.018
[woman] There being
111 ayes and 22 nays,

01:06:28.052 --> 01:06:30.687
the bill is passed as amended
by conference and its title

01:06:30.720 --> 01:06:32.822
agreed to.
[gavel bangs]

01:06:32.856 --> 01:06:39.063
*uplifting music

01:06:39.096 --> 01:06:41.665
When we heard the final
verdict that it passed,

01:06:41.698 --> 01:06:43.167
it was a celebration.

01:06:43.200 --> 01:06:45.001
It was like
fireworks going off.

01:06:45.035 --> 01:06:46.870
It was like the final chapter.

01:06:46.903 --> 01:06:50.174
You know, it was
like the conclusion.

01:06:50.207 --> 01:06:53.177
It was like,
"Okay, we've done it."

01:06:53.210 --> 01:06:59.015
***

01:06:59.049 --> 01:07:01.051
[man VO] So
what comes next?

01:07:01.085 --> 01:07:06.556
We're really, really excited
to have created a bill

01:07:06.590 --> 01:07:07.957
and...

01:07:07.991 --> 01:07:11.728
to have other states
wanting to replicate it.

01:07:11.761 --> 01:07:15.932
I helped Maine and
Colorado with their bills,

01:07:15.965 --> 01:07:19.736
and there's other states
that want to have a similar

01:07:19.769 --> 01:07:21.805
bill to Alec's.

01:07:21.838 --> 01:07:25.575
Tina Smith is really working
hard to create something similar

01:07:25.609 --> 01:07:27.911
on the federal level.

01:07:27.944 --> 01:07:30.447
Pharma's
challenging the bill and,

01:07:30.480 --> 01:07:32.582
you know, suing the
state of Minnesota.

01:07:32.616 --> 01:07:34.584
***

01:07:34.618 --> 01:07:38.455
You know, it's been a really
rough four years. [chuckles]

01:07:38.488 --> 01:07:40.624
Um...

01:07:40.657 --> 01:07:42.592
I was-- I was a
shell of a person.

01:07:42.626 --> 01:07:44.094
I was not...

01:07:44.128 --> 01:07:47.931
I was not capable
of being a mom.

01:07:47.964 --> 01:07:51.935
[voice wavering] I-- I
needed to-- to mourn,

01:07:51.968 --> 01:07:56.072
and I needed to grieve,
and I needed to escape.

01:07:56.106 --> 01:07:57.741
[sniffles]

01:07:57.774 --> 01:08:00.777
Um...
[sighs]

01:08:03.147 --> 01:08:07.917
And my advocacy was a way
for me to-- to do that.

01:08:07.951 --> 01:08:11.121
***

01:08:11.155 --> 01:08:13.790
Since Alec's bill
been passed into law,

01:08:13.823 --> 01:08:17.827
over 600 people's been
saved-- their lives' been saved.

01:08:18.128 --> 01:08:20.997
So the bill is working.

01:08:21.030 --> 01:08:22.932
[man] How proud does
that make you feel?

01:08:22.966 --> 01:08:25.969
Very proud.
Ecstatic.

01:08:26.170 --> 01:08:28.638
I know Alec is watching.

01:08:28.672 --> 01:08:30.940
And he's saying,
"Nobody else."

01:08:30.974 --> 01:08:33.143
He's an angel.

01:08:33.643 --> 01:08:36.112
But you know, the fight doesn't
stop just because we won this

01:08:36.146 --> 01:08:37.347
small battle.

01:08:37.381 --> 01:08:41.151
You know, we still have a war
to win and-- and ultimately,

01:08:41.185 --> 01:08:44.521
we don't stop fighting
until we've won that.

01:08:44.554 --> 01:08:50.994
-[fireworks]
-[bell ringing]

01:08:51.995 --> 01:08:53.129
[James] Hey!

01:08:53.163 --> 01:08:54.298
How y'all doing?

01:08:54.331 --> 01:08:56.166
Glad y'all could make it!

01:08:56.200 --> 01:08:58.668
[Nicole] 4th of July at our
house tends to be a big

01:08:58.702 --> 01:09:00.837
celebration.

01:09:00.870 --> 01:09:03.006
[Nicole] Come to grandma!

01:09:03.039 --> 01:09:05.141
[Nicole VO] It's just a way
to celebrate Alec since it was

01:09:05.175 --> 01:09:08.011
his favorite holiday.

01:09:08.044 --> 01:09:09.679
[Nicole] Food is ready
for whomever would like

01:09:09.713 --> 01:09:11.014
to make a plate!

01:09:11.047 --> 01:09:12.015
[woman] It all looks so good!

01:09:12.048 --> 01:09:13.116
[Nicole VO] It's a
time for people to...

01:09:13.149 --> 01:09:16.553
to share stories of
Alec and to remember him.

01:09:16.586 --> 01:09:19.022
Alec, he couldn't get
into that damn house!

01:09:19.055 --> 01:09:20.156
[laughs]

01:09:20.190 --> 01:09:21.325
This is one of
his best friends.

01:09:21.358 --> 01:09:24.060
[laughs]

01:09:24.093 --> 01:09:25.895
[Nicole VO] You know,
it can be a lot of fun,

01:09:25.929 --> 01:09:27.697
but it could also be really sad.

01:09:27.731 --> 01:09:30.734
-[James] I love you.
-I love you too, man.

01:09:30.767 --> 01:09:31.668
[James] You know what?

01:09:31.701 --> 01:09:34.170
Tonight, we celebrate
the bill passing.

01:09:34.204 --> 01:09:36.039
No one else has to die

01:09:36.072 --> 01:09:39.008
because they can't
afford insulin.

01:09:39.042 --> 01:09:42.045
My son's not with me...

01:09:42.078 --> 01:09:46.049
in the body, but
he's in my spirit.

01:09:47.050 --> 01:09:48.585
Long live Al.

01:09:48.618 --> 01:09:51.255
-[group] Long live Al!
-[James] Long live Al.

01:09:51.888 --> 01:09:54.057
Yup.

01:09:54.090 --> 01:09:56.025
-That's a fact!
-Love you, bro!

01:09:56.059 --> 01:09:56.860
[James] Love you!

01:09:56.893 --> 01:09:58.562
We're always connected.

01:10:03.900 --> 01:10:05.369
[James] Mm.

01:10:05.402 --> 01:10:07.103
Mm!

01:10:09.739 --> 01:10:11.741
You ready?!

01:10:15.078 --> 01:10:20.884
[fireworks popping
and blaring]

01:10:20.917 --> 01:10:22.252
Tell 'em!

01:10:23.753 --> 01:10:25.789
Tell 'em!

01:10:25.822 --> 01:10:34.598
*uplifting music

01:11:01.291 --> 01:11:08.298
*heartwarming mellow music

01:11:46.169 --> 01:11:57.681
*ethereal music
